<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-764-946  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 764 946.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Information Week  August 13 1990 n282 p51(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Groupe Bull sees red: company reports loss amid majororganizational changes.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hoffman, Thomas.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>French computer company Groupe Bull S.A., parent firm of Bull HNInformation Systems Inc of Billerica, MA, has a net loss of $331million for the six months ended Jun 30, 1990, compared to a netloss of $94 million for the same period in 1989.andP;  The firm had atotal revenue of $2.8 billion for the first half of 1990, whichrepresents a gain on revenue of $2.5 billion reported for thefirst half of 1989.andP;  A market shift away from proprietary systemsand several organizational changes are seen as reasons for thefinancial performance.andP;  International reorganization will spurmanagement to lay off 3,000 of the firm's 50,000 employees to belaid off by the end of 1990.andP;  Users in the information technologymarket are migrating toward standards-based products thatrepresent low profit for vendors.andP;  Bull has recently releasedproducts that answer the need for standardization among users.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Compagnie des Machines Bull (finance)Bull HN Information Systems Inc. (finance).andO;Topic:     LayoffFinancial StabilityReorganizationStandardizationUser NeedsLosses.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>